The statement by Press Secretary Jay Carney reflects on the third anniversary of the Great East Japan Earthquake. It acknowledges the suffering caused by the tragedy and offers condolences to the families and friends of those who lost their lives. The statement emphasizes the support and assistance provided by the United States, including over $100 million in government aid and private donations. It also highlights the enduring friendship between the United States and Japan and the commitment to the U.S.-Japan alliance for peace and security in the Asia-Pacific region. The United States is ready to continue assisting Japan in the cleanup at the Fukushima site and in determining the future of their energy economy. The statement concludes by expressing thoughts and prayers for the people of Japan on this anniversary.